Singer, songwriter, musician and Dancer, Omoniyi Temidayo Rapheal also known as Zlatan Ibile, has wowed Nigerians as he inks himself with the image of the first president of Ghana Dr Kwame Nkrumah. Taking to his instagram, @zlatan_ibile he shares a photo of the tatoo he had gotten. Inscribed on the right side of his chest is the face of the Former President Nkrumah. Kwame Nkrumah PC was a Ghanaian politician and revolutionary. He was the first Prime Minister and President of Ghana, having led the Gold Coast to independence from Britain in 1957. He headed the country from independence in 1957 until he was overthrown by a coup in 1966 and later died on April 27, 1972, in Bucharest, Romania.